My sweet precious David

.ue 2
                                                                       $.#$
Forts.: 31 Jany 59.
This is to be your sonder letter and no one's else, for my David self. For
I heard, that you dont like to have in common your letters, which I quite
understand.

It is now 2 years, that we took you on board ship and had to take that sad,
very sad adieu for long, very long time. O my sweet David, it is still be-
fore me, as if it had happened but a few days ago; but I must not think of
it, else I become too nervous.

I was greatly rejoiced to hear that you are obedient to your dear new Papa
and Mama, that they can say of my own ____________621: he is a good boy and
likes to learn; to hear such testimony is my greatest pleasure.
.fo -
